cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use this software or the datalake it builds, please cite it as below."
title: "tropes-removal-model"
abstract: >-
  A pre-commit/CI gate that detects AI-writing tropes (per tropes.fyi's
  33-pattern catalog) in text, going hybrid: ~21 lexical/structural/
  formatting tropes are caught by deterministic ONNX RegexFullMatch nodes
  (zero training data, verified 0 mismatches vs Python's re.search across
  30,000 real sentences), and ~12 genuinely semantic tropes by a SetFit
  few-shot classifier (contrastive sentence-transformer fine-tuning + a
  lightweight head, chosen for its sample efficiency over full end-to-end
  fine-tuning). Both branches plus a FLAN-T5 rewriter are exported to ONNX,
  backed by an Essential-Tuple-Normal-Form parquet+zstd datalake built from
  public corpora (HC3, artem9k/ai-text-detection-pile, RAID) and
  hand-authored synthetic examples covering all 33 catalog entries.
authors:
  - family-names: Lee
    given-names: "K. S. Ernest (iFire)"
license: MIT
